.TH "get_default_font" 9 "get_default_font" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
get_default_font \- get default font
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const struct font_desc *" get_default_font
.BI "(int xres "  ","
.BI "int yres "  ","
.BI "u32 font_w "  ","
.BI "u32 font_h "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xres" 12
screen size of X
.IP "yres" 12
screen size of Y
.IP "font_w" 12
bit array of supported widths (1 - 32)
.IP "font_h" 12
bit array of supported heights (1 - 32)

Get the default font for a specified screen size.
Dimensions are in pixels.

Returns NULL if no font is found, or a pointer to the
chosen font.
